.TH "createCL" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" "Version 2.9"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
createCL \- Create a new collection.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]db.collectionspace.createCL(<name>,[options])\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
Collection Space
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Create a collection in a specified collection space.
Collection is a logical object which stores records.
Each record should belong to one and only one collection.
.SH PARAMETERS
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]name\f[] ( \f[I]String\f[] , \f[I]Required\f[] )
.RS 2
.PP
The name of the collection, should be unique to each other in a collection
space.
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]options\f[] ( \f[I]Object\f[], \f[I]Optional\f[] )
.RS 2
.PP
The options for creating the collection, could be a combination of the following
options:
.IP " 1." 4
\f[C]ShardingKey\f[] ( \f[I]Object\f[] ): The sharding key of the collection.
.RS 4
.PP
Format: \f[C]ShardingKey:{<field1>\ :\ <1|\-1>,[<field1>\ :\ <1|\-1>,\ ...]}\f[]
.RE
.IP " 2." 4
\f[C]ShardingType\f[] ( \f[I]String\f[] ): The sharding type of the collection,
could be one of the following:
.RS 4
.IP \[bu] 2
"hash": Sharding by hash.
.IP \[bu] 2
"range": Sharding by range.
.PP
Format: \f[C]ShardingType:"hash"|"range"\f[]
.RE
.IP " 3." 4
\f[C]Partition\f[] ( \f[I]Int32\f[] ): Specify the number of hash slices, only
valid when \f[C]ShardingType\f[] is "hash".
The number of hash slices should be power of 2 and in the range of [2^3，2^20],
default to be 1024.
.RS 4
.PP
Format: \f[C]Partition:\ <num>\f[]
.RE
.IP " 4." 4
\f[C]ReplSize\f[] ( \f[I]Int32\f[] ): Number of WriteConcern, default to be 1,
can be one of the follow:
.RS 4
.IP \[bu] 2
\-1: WriteConcern equals to the number of the active nodes in the replica group.
.IP \[bu] 2
0: WriteConcern equals to the number of all the nodes in replica group.
.IP \[bu] 2
1 \- 7: WriteConcern = 1\-7.
.PP
Format: \f[C]ReplSize:\ <num>\f[]
.RE
.IP " 5." 4
\f[C]Compressed\f[] ( \f[I]Bool\f[] ): Compress the collection or not, default
to be false.
.RS 4
.PP
Format: \f[C]Compressed:true|false\f[]
.RE
.IP " 6." 4
\f[C]CompressionType\f[] ( \f[I]String\f[] ): The algorithm for compressing,
default to be "snappy", can be one of the follow:
.RS 4
.IP \[bu] 2
"snappy": use snappy algorithm to compress.
.IP \[bu] 2
"lzw": use lzw algorithm to compress.
.PP
Format: \f[C]CompressionType:"snappy"|"lzw"\f[]
.RE
.IP " 7." 4
\f[C]IsMainCL\f[] ( \f[I]Bool\f[] ): Is main collection or not, default to be
false.
.RS 4
.PP
Format: \f[C]IsMainCL:true|false\f[]
.RE
.IP " 8." 4
\f[C]AutoSplit\f[] ( \f[I]Bool\f[] ): Automatic split or not, default to be
false.
.RS 4
.PP
Format: \f[C]AutoSplit:true|false\f[]
.RE
.IP " 9." 4
\f[C]Group\f[] ( \f[I]String\f[] ): Specify a replica group which the collection
should be in.
.RS 4
.PP
Format: \f[C]Group:<group\ name>\f[]
.RE
.IP "10." 4
\f[C]AutoIndexId\f[] ( \f[I]Bool\f[] ): Creating unique index by using field
"_id" or not, default to be true.
.RS 4
.PP
Format: \f[C]AutoIndexId:true|false\f[]
.RE
.IP "11." 4
\f[C]EnsureShardingIndex\f[] ( \f[I]Bool\f[] ): Creating index by using the
fields of the \f[C]ShardingKey\f[] or not, default to be true.
.RS 4
.PP
Format: \f[C]EnsureShardingIndex:true|false\f[]
.RE
.IP "12." 4
\f[C]StrictDataMode\f[] ( \f[I]Bool\f[] ): using strict date mode in numeric operations 
or not, default to be false.
.RS 4
.PP
Format: \f[C]StrictDataMode:true|false\f[]
.RE
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[]
.IP \[bu] 2
The parameter \f[C]name\f[] can not be an empty string, and can not include "."
or "$"; The length of it should not be greater than 127B, or exception will
occur.
.IP \[bu] 2
The parameter \f[C]options\f[] haves one or more fields, please use comma(,) to
separate.
.IP \[bu] 2
AutoSplit must cooperate with hash partitioning and domain.
.IP \[bu] 2
AutoSplit and Group cannot be set at the same time.
.IP \[bu] 2
If AutoSplit is not specified in a collection, the value of AutoSplit will
come from domain.
.IP \[bu] 2
If AutoSplit is specified in a collection which is belong to a domain, the
value of AutoSplit will cover the AutoSplit value of domain.
.IP \[bu] 2
If AutoSplit is specified in a collection which is not belong to any domain,
the collection will be splitted into all groups of SYSDOMAIN.
.IP \[bu] 2
Group must exist in a domain, which contains a collection space, which has the
group(All replica group belong to SYSDOMAIN, that is to say, a collection space
can be distributed into any replica group if no specific group is given)
.RE
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
On success, createCL() creates a new collection and return the object.
.PP
On error, exception will be thrown.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
