.PP
When error happen, use getLastErrMsg() to get the error message or use
getLastError() to get the error code.
See troubleshooting for more detail.
.SH HISTORY
.PP
Since v1.0.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP "1." 3
Create collection "bar" in collection space "foo" without shard key.
If the collection space "foo" doesn\[aq]t exist, it will automatically generate
collection space "foo".
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.foo.createCL("bar")
localhost:11810.foo.bar
Takes\ 0.1250s.
\f[]
.fi
.RE
.IP "2." 3
Create a compressed normal collection "bar" in collection space "foo" with the
hash shard key "age" and in ascending order, using 65535 partitions with
writeconcern 1.
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.foo.createCL("bar",{ShardingKey:{age:1},ShardingType:"hash",
\ \ Partition:65535,\ ReplSize:1,\ Compressed:true,\ IsMainCL:false})
localhost:11810.foo.bar
Takes\ 0.32450s.
\f[]
.fi
.RE
.IP "3." 3
Create collection "bar" in collection space "foo" with the StrictDataMode trun on.
If the collection space "foo" doesn\[aq]t exist, it will automatically generate
collection space "foo".
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.foo.createCL("bar", { StrictDataMode: true})
localhost:11810.foo.bar
Takes\ 0.1250s.
\f[]
.fi
.RE
